          .component-block#start
            .mb-5
              hr.mb-5
              h3 Getting started
              p.lead The template is using Gulp to automate the development and build processes. All you should do to start your project is to open the terminal in the root directory (where the package.json file is located) and enter fallowing commands.
            .mb-5
              pre
                code.language-markup
                  |npm install -g gulp
                  |
                  |&lt;!-- When you&rsquo;re done, make sure you&rsquo;ve installed the rest of the theme&rsquo;s dependencies: --&gt;
                  |
                  |npm install
                  |
                  |&lt;!-- Start. Be aware that this replaces existing &quot;dist&quot; files, so proceed with caution. --&gt;
                  |
                  |gulp
              p *Note. You should already have #[a(href="https://nodejs.org/en/") Node] installed in your machine to build the project.
